    "What is the atomic structure?"
  ],
  "responses": [
    "The structure of an atom consists of three main components:\n1. Nucleus: The central core of the atom, containing protons and neutrons.\n2. Electrons: Tiny, negatively charged particles that orbit the nucleus in electron shells or energy levels.\n3. Protons: Positively charged particles found in the nucleus.\n4. Neutrons: Neutrally charged particles also located in the nucleus.\nThe arrangement of these components determines the identity and properties of the element."
